In theScriptor, Norman. Veteres, by Du Cheſn. f. 10. 6.

                  Eſtabliſhment or Charter of Roven, and Falaiſe in Normandy, the Government of the City and Town was by a Mayor, Twenty Four Jurats, (ſo called, becauſe ſworn, &c. when they were choſen and admitted) and an Hundred Pares or Peers. The Twenty Four Jurats were annually choſen, out of the 100 Peers, by the 100 Peers;
                  What the Community of Roven in Normandy was. whereof Twelve were Eſchevins, that is, Aldermen, and the other Twelve, Conſultores, Counſellors, and all theſe together were called the Communia, or Community of that City, and Town with the Caſtle.
